full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/28/2023 HOUSTON COMMUNITY COLLEGE SYSTEM SOUTHEAST COLLEGE N.T.O. INS# 1275-91 August 7, 1997 Citizenship Office Alien Number: 028621564 JOSE A ROMAN 13325 SW 47 ST MIAMI FL 33175 -This is an important letter. Present it at the time of your naturalization interview.- Dear JOSE A ROMAN: CONGRATULATIONS. You have passed your standardized citizenship test. This puts you another step closer to becoming a naturalized citizen. Passing the Southeast College test means that certain educational requirements of the Immigration and Nationality Act have been met. However, you must still be found eligible in all other ways by the U.S. Immigration and Naturalization Service. I thank you for participating in the Southeast College, National Testing Organization, program. We appreciate the confidence you have shown in us and hope that the remainder of your journey to becoming a United States citizen goes smoothly. Sincerely, Test Date: 7/26/97 Test Site: H045 Jean Jean W. W. Vining, thing Ed. D. Test Administrator: T VEREA Interim Director, Southeast College Test Location: HIALEAH FL National Testing Organization gew 7015 Gulf Frwy., Suite 138, Houston, TX 77087 (713) 718-7588; FAX: (713) 718-7014
